The American Sadder for Women’s Health estimates that more than 2,500 girls or younger people are being detained for “crossing a border offense” across Latin America. Women residing in poor cities and municipalities of Uruguay have limited access to many healthcare services. Working moms from the informal sector with restrictive financial revenue, few alternative assets and inadequate employment rights are marginalized in the health system.
